<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.5045/27: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-15T14:00:00-05:00">December 15, 1929—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>116. All quiet. <hi rend="italic">Galveston</hi> arrived Port-au-Prince
                            this morning. I have requested <hi rend="italic">Galveston</hi> to sail
                            afternoon 16th to arrive [Gonaives?] morning of 17th, sail from Gonaives
                            noon 17th when she will be released from duty in Haitian waters.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>